Description:
The 4-port network analyser will form the heart of the measurement facility providing the transmitter and receiver for the antenna system, as a standalone facility to measure S-parameters, material properties, circuit characteristics etc. Millimeter wave extension modules will provide frequency coverage to 110 GHz. The equipment to be procured will form a facility to measure devices, antennas, circuits and materials in the frequency range up to 110 GHz. It is important that equipment will measure on-wafer antennas and devices before and after bonding/packaging. It is important that all the equipment is compatible with each other (see dependencies within the ITT) The three items of equipment to be purchased under separate tenders are:

1) Antenna Measurement System NSI-700S-360 system (already sourced);
2) Vector network analyser;
3) Probe station.

This tender specification is offered as an invitation to tender for a service agreement with Sheffield Hallam University to deliver a training programme, through the engagement of a PhD cohort, that increases the aspirations of higher ability school students and to create a suite of teaching resources for wider dissemination.  There are two specific objectives;
* Sessions with Students - To recruit PhD students from the University of Sheffield and Sheffield Hallam University to deliver educational sessions to HeppSY+ targeted school students in order to;  expand their knowledge of research topics, develop their research skills and increase their interest and confidence in applying for a higher tariff university. 
* Resource Development - To create a range of resources based on	various PhD research topics, map these to national curriculum subjects, and make them available for delivery by teachers in HeppSY+ target schools. These materials will; enhance curriculum delivery, promote positive progression to higher education, be available as on-line web based resources and should lead to increased teacher confidence when discussing HE options with their students.
